#Text=UEFA Champions League 2006/07 : AC Milan 1-0
#Text=Celtic
#Text=Wednesday , March 7 , 2007
#Text=AC Milan
#Text=1(1 )
#Text=0(0 )

#Text=Attendance

#Text=65000 Goalscorers for AC Milan Kaka ( 93 ' ) Goalscorers for Celtic None Bookings ( AC Milan ) Ambrosini ( Yellow ( 1 ) ) Bookings ( Celtic ) McManus , Naylor , McGeady , Lennon ( Yellow ( 4 ) )
#Text=A full crowd showed up at the Guiseppe Meazza in Italy today to watch AC Milan take on Scottish side Celtic .
#Text=The first leg of the matches ended in a goalless draw , as both teams were spirited in defense .
#Text=Kaka and Inzaghi played as frontmen for AC , while Vennegoor of Hesselink and Jiri Jarosik were the strike pair for Celtic .
#Text=Milan had the first chance of the game early when Kaka found room and flashed a shot towards the bottom corner , but keeper Artur Boruc got down well to make the stop .
#Text=Celtic then had a valid penalty claim after only 6 minutes when Jarosik 's volley looked to be blocked by the hand of Maldini , but referee Konrad Plautz waved away the appeals .
#Text=Celtic 's defense continued to play well , and they limited Milan 's chances to long ranged shots .
#Text=Lee Naylor then performed defensive heroics for Celtic as he took the ball away from the open Inzaghi , who was waiting to tap the ball in at the back post .
#Text=Kaka had two more shots from range at the net , but neither were on target .
#Text=Naylor again saved Celtic by clearing the ball off the line from a Kaka attempt .
#Text=Over an hour had passed when Gord Strachan sent Thomas Graveson on for Celtic in place of Jarosik , and the Dane almost scored right away .
#Text=He struck a fine shot at the net , but Massimo Oddo did well to block the attempt .
#Text=Milan counter attacked quickly , and Kaka saw his attempt also blocked by a defender .
#Text=McManus and Naylor were forced to clear headers off the line from Ambrosini and Inzaghi , both occurring after corners .
#Text=Maldini then had a header at the Celtic net , but Boruc was again in the right place to make the stop .
#Text=Celtic had another claim for a penalty when Nakamura was brought down in the area , but the Austrian referee again waved away all appeals .
#Text=Boruc was again forced into action from a Seedorf free kick , which he was able to deflect out with a hand .
#Text=Kaka then shot towards the goal , but the crossbar saved Celtic from going a goal down .
#Text=As 90 minutes approached , Celtic had two well positioned free-kicks , but could take advantage of neither , and the game entered extra time .
#Text=It took Milan little time to go ahead in the extra period , and the scorer would be no other than the Brazilian Kaka .
#Text=The youthful striker put on a burst of speed to beat out the tired Celtic defenders and blasted the ball through Borucs legs to give the homeside the lead .
#Text=The game continued however , as the Champions League works on full extra time , and Celtic still had 27 minutes to equalize .
#Text=It was Milan who pushed however , and Andrea Pirlo twice forced Boruc to make saves .
#Text=Then Kaka , in search of a brace , sent a volley over the net after being left alone during a corner kick .
#Text=Gravesen 's long effort for Celtic was easy pickings for Dida , and Craig Beattie headed a good chance over the bar .
#Text=Celtic vainly tried to tie the game , bringing on Kenny Miller , but AC finished the game comfortably , and advanced to the next round of the tournament .
